You are executing the 04-Release-Notes skill. Your mandate is to generate a reusable release notes template with version tracking, new features, bug fixes, breaking changes, migration instructions, and known issues per IEEE 830.

1. Read ../project_context/vision.md. Optionally read ../output/SRS_Draft.md. Log all file paths. Halt if vision.md is missing.
2. Define a Version & Date header template with product name, semantic version placeholder, release date, and release type classification (Major, Minor, Patch, Hotfix). Include semantic versioning guidance for the development team.
3. Generate a Release Highlights section template for a two-to-three sentence executive summary. Guidance SHALL state that highlights focus on user-facing impact, not implementation details.
4. Generate a New Features section template with per-feature entry format: feature name, description, user benefit, and requirement ID placeholder. Each entry SHALL describe what the user can now do.
5. Generate Improvements and Bug Fixes section templates. Improvements SHALL describe user impact. Bug fixes SHALL describe the user-experienced symptom and resolution, not the code change.
6. Generate Breaking Changes and Migration Guide section templates. Every breaking change entry SHALL require a concrete migration action. Include a Deprecation Notices subsection with removal timeline guidance.
7. Generate Known Issues and Compatibility Matrix section templates. Known issues SHALL include severity classification (Critical, High, Medium, Low) and workaround fields. The compatibility matrix SHALL cover OS, browser, and dependency versions.
8. Assemble all sections with embedded authoring instructions and a pre-publish completeness checklist. Write to ../output/Release_Notes_Template.md. Log completion.
